title: Everyone’s scared of AI taking over. Here’s what no one’s talking about!

author: Aevy TV

Across the world, birthrates are falling—even as populations keep rising for now. This video dives into the paradox: from Japan’s ghost villages and South Korea’s record-low fertility to India’s looming OADR shift, we map how fewer births ripple into schools, jobs, taxes, and power. We unpack the “why” beyond “it’s expensive”: contraception and choice, changing marriage norms, career incentives, hypergamy debates, climate dread—and yes, the real rupee cost of raising a child in 2025.
We track the financial, emotional, and opportunity trade-offs, then zoom out to policy misfires (Romania’s Ceaușescu era) and the coming demographic center of gravity in Africa. This isn’t pro or anti-kids; it’s about making an informed choice with eyes wide open.

Watch till the end for a grounded, human conclusion that brings the debate home.
